.TH RELAY 1 "July 2026" "Activity-Relay" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
relay \- operate an ActivityPub relay server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B relay
[\fB--config\fR \fIPATH\fR] \fIserver|worker|control\fR
.br
.B relay generate-key
[\fB--output\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB--bits\fR \fIBITS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B relay
runs the Activity-Relay API server, delivery worker, and control utility.
The Debian package installs inactive systemd units and an example configuration
under /etc/activity-relay.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B server
Run the ActivityPub API and inbox server.
.TP
.B worker
Run queued delivery workers.
.TP
.B control
Manage relay policy, domains, and follow requests.
.TP
.B generate-key
Create a PKCS#1 RSA actor identity without replacing an existing key.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/activity-relay/config.yml
Operator configuration, created from config.yml.example.
.TP
.I /etc/activity-relay/actor.pem
Relay cryptographic identity generated during initial package installation.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR redis-server (1)
